definition:
Someone descended from Merari who was a man of the tribe of Levi living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, first mentioned at Gen.46.11; 
 son of: Levi (H3878); 
 brother of: Gershon (H1648), Kohath (H6955) and Jochebed (H3115); 
 father of: Mahli (H4249), Mushi (H4187) and Jaaziah (H3269)
Another name of me.ra.ri (מְרָרִי "Merari" H4847) 
 § Merarites, of Marari "bitter"
 descendants of Merari, the son of Levi, and members of a Levitical family
